# Quality Gate — Mandatory Post-Completion Review

After completing a feature, multi-step task, or significant refactor (3+ files changed), **immediately** run the quality-review skill (`/.cursor/skills/quality-review/SKILL.md`) before reporting completion to the user.

Do not wait for the user to ask. Do not skip it. Treat it as the final step of every major task.

**Workflow:**
1. Finish implementation
2. Run quality-review checklist (security, a11y, SEO, i18n, code quality, config)
3. Fix any issues found
4. Then report to the user — include a brief QA summary with any fixes made
